The Port of NAIA, Bureau of Customs cleared 500,000 doses of Sinovac vaccines, which arrived on April 22, 2021 via Flight No. PR361 from Beijing, China. Vaccine Czar Secretary Carlito G.  Galvez Jr. welcomed the arrival of the vaccines.
